  "description": "A morphism class in the predicate category, induced by the diagonal collapse (s, o) ↦ (o, o) on the entity-pair index. Builds a binary predicate q whose value at (s, o) depends only on p's value at (o, o), broadcasting the object-diagonal content. The dual of subject-projection. One of the four canonical generators of the predicate category.",
